[practice id="res://course/lesson-4-drawing-a-rectangle/practice-5AJTESv5.tres" title="Drawing a Rectangle"]
[description]Based on your rectangle corner, you now need to draw a complete rectangle.[/description]
[goal]
Add the correct arguments to the functions [code]move_forward()[/code] and [code]turn_right()[/code] to draw a rectangle with a width of [code]200[/code] pixels, and a height of [code]120[/code] pixels.

We wrote the first argument for you.

In the next practice, you'll use the same functions to draw a bigger rectangle.
[/goal]
[starting_code]
func draw_rectangle():
	move_forward(200)
	turn_right()
	move_forward()
	turn_right()
	move_forward()
	turn_right()
	move_forward()
[/starting_code]
