[practice id="res://course/lesson-4-drawing-a-rectangle/practice-kGx0c7DD.tres" title="Drawing a Bigger Rectangle"]
[description]At this point, you're ready to code entirely on your own. Call functions by yourself to draw a complete rectangle.[/description]
[goal]
Write out calls to the functions [code]move_forward()[/code] and [code]turn_right()[/code] to draw a rectangle with a width of 220 pixels, and a height of 260 pixels.

We wrote the first two lines for you.

Be sure to write each instruction on a separate line.

Every line should start with one [code]Tab[/code] character so the computer understands it's part of the [code]draw_rectangle()[/code] function.
[/goal]
[starting_code]
func draw_rectangle():
	move_forward(220)
	turn_right(90)
[/starting_code]
